  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ombudsman DK-RI and DHF: Exchange of Experience on Accessibility and Inclusion of Persons with Disabilities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the project is for the Ombudsman of the Republic of Indonesia (ORI) to improve its services to be inclusive and accessible for persons with disabilities.

The project is a joint collaboration between The Ombudsman of the Republic of Indonesia (ORI), the Danish Parliamentary Ombudsman (DPO) and the Danish Association of the Physically Disabled (DHF).

The grant will support three outputs: development guidelines how to provide inclusive service, increased knowledge within ORI on how to improve complaint handling for persons with disabilities, and a comparative report. These three outputs will be reached through 3 workshops, 1 training, and 1 comparative study.</narrative>
  </description>
